                    "company": "Utrecht University",
                    "description": "My PhD project is part of the Beyond Sharia: The Role of Sufism in Shaping Islam ERC Advanced Grant Project under the leadership of prof.dr. Asghar Seyed-Gohrab at Utrecht University. Our team consists of 4 PhD and 3 PostDoc candidates. Together we will investigate the emergence, flourishing and lasting appeal of non-conformist movements in Islamic intellectual history from the 10th century to the present day.\n\nMy own research on \u2018Literary Qalandars\u2019 will explore antinomian motifs, metaphors, imagery, and stories (which are meant to challenge the religious hierarchy and orthodox Islam) in Persian poetry from the 12th century onward. To this day, this poetry has had a great appeal to Muslims in the Persian world and far beyond. I also analyse how qalandari (Sufi saints at a high level of spirituality) themes in this poetry impacted social, political and religious developments in subsequent centuries.",
                    "title": "PhD Candidate",
                    "employment_type": "Full-time"
                }
            ]
        },
